<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="297" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,152,591]" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,429,452]" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">Discussion.</emphasis>
This new species can be distinguished from known species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zeuner" authorityYear="1940" box="[1032,1178,429,452]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Phlugiolopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1032,1178,429,452]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">Phlugiolopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by: basal area of male cercus stout, subsequently divided into two lobes, dorsal lobe slightly short, nearly rectangular, while ventral lobe broad basally, tapering, 1/3 apical area narrow, bent upwards and twisted; posterior margin of subgenital plate obtusely rounded, with conical styli on ventral surface of subapex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
